java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>, java.util.Set<E>
public class ListenableSet<E>
extends java.util.AbstractSet<E>

A set which can be listened to for changes. Whenever an object is added or removed from the set a CollectionChangeEvent is fired to all listeners. For the purpose of CollectionChangeEvents there is no reference value

See Also:
CollectionChangeEvent, CollectionChangeListener
